11-32-101. Definitions.

(a) As used in this act:

(i) "Baby poultry" means poultry under ten (10) weeks of age;

(ii) "Board" means the Wyoming livestock board;

(iii) "Breeding stock" means poultry used for reproduction;

(iv) "Poultry" means live chickens, turkeys, ducks, geese and game birds as defined by W.S. 23-1-101(a)(iv);

(v) "This act" means W.S. 11-32-101 through 11-32-104.
